Privacy Policy
Last Updated: March 17, 2026
This Privacy Policy describes how we handle information in the القرآن الكريم (Quran) mobile application (the "App").
1. No Data Collection
We believe in your privacy. The App is designed to function entirely offline and does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information, usage data, or device identifiers to us or any third party.
2. Local Storage (Bookmarks)
The App allows you to save "Bookmarks" to track your reading progress.
•
How it works: This data is stored locally on your device using Android SharedPreferences.
•
Control: This data never leaves your device. You can clear this data at any time by clearing the App's cache/data in your device settings or by uninstalling the App.
3. Permissions
The App does not require any sensitive permissions (such as Location, Camera, or Contacts) to function. It only requires standard access to its own internal assets to display the Quranic text.
4. Third-Party Services
The App does not use any third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, or cloud-tracking services.
5. Children’s Privacy
Since we do not collect any personal information, the App is safe for users of all ages, including children. We do not knowingly or unknowingly collect data from children under the age of 13.
6. Changes to This Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in this document with a new "Last Updated" date.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or suggestions about this Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at: salmanebaba@outlook.com.